Documentation for this format

element.definition: A document that contains information about a product being submitted for approval to the FDA.

constraint.human: All FHIR elements must have a @value or children

element.definition: Unique id for the element within a resource (for internal references). This may be any string value that does not contain spaces.

slicing.description: Extensions are always sliced by (at least) url

element.definition: May be used to represent additional information that is not part of the basic definition of the element. To make the use of extensions safe and manageable, there is a strict set of governance  applied to the definition and use of extensions. Though any implementer can define an extension, there is a set of requirements that SHALL be met as part of the definition of the extension.
element.comment: There can be no stigma associated with the use of extensions by any application, project, or standard - regardless of the institution or jurisdiction that uses or defines the extensions.  The use of extensions is what allows the FHIR specification to retain a core level of simplicity for everyone.

constraint.human: All FHIR elements must have a @value or children
Must have either extensions or value[x], not both

element.definition: A unique identifier of this specific Product Submission document.
A date reference to the SPL version being used for this document.
A unique identifier of the submission that remains constant across all versions/revisions of this document.
An integer that provides a sequence to the versions of the submission document.
A LOINC code that provides inforamtion on the Product Submission type.
The title for the document.
Information about the labeler organization that authored the document.
The Duns & Broadstreet number for the labeler organization.
The name of the labeler organization.
Information about the registrant organization associated with the labeler.
The Duns & Broadstreet number for the registrant organization.
The name of the registrant organization.
Information about the establishment organization associated with active or new marketed products.
The Duns & Broadstreet number for the establishment organization.
The name of the establishment organization.
Various business operations that the Establishment organization performs.
A code representing the specific business operation that the Establishment organization can perform.
The NDC code of the specific product that this business operation is about.
Reference to other documents that contain relevant information about this product submission.
A unique identifier of this related document.
A unique identifier of the submission of this related document.
An integer that provides a sequence to the versions of the related document.
A logical grouping of Product Submission information.
An identifier for this section that can be used to reference it in the document.
The date when this section was authored.
A code that identifies the content conveyed in this section.
A header for the content contained in this section.
The human readable content of this section.
Content that is not a complete rendering of the information in this section.
References to images that are used in the human readable content of this section.
Title of the image.
Reference, either local or remote, to the image data.
Sub-groupings of the content contained in a section.
